  <p>
    For a precise calculation based on your personal situation, use our <a href="/en/">net salary calculator</a>.
  </p>

  <h2 id="higher-income-example">Higher Income Example: RAL &euro;50,000 in Rome</h2>

  <p>
    To illustrate the impact of higher IRPEF brackets and regional surcharges, let us consider <strong>Alessandro</strong>, a single software engineer with no dependents, resident in <strong>Rome (Lazio)</strong>, with a <strong>RAL of &euro;50,000</strong> on 13 pay periods. Lazio is one of the most expensive regions for tax purposes, with a progressive regional surcharge that reaches <strong>3.33%</strong> on the highest income brackets. Rome also applies a municipal surcharge of <strong>0.9%</strong>. Here is the full breakdown:
  </p>

  <p>
    <strong>Step 1 &mdash; INPS contributions:</strong> &euro;50,000 &times; 9.19% = <strong>&euro;4,595</strong>.
  </p>
  <p>
    <strong>Step 2 &mdash; Taxable income:</strong> &euro;50,000 &minus; &euro;4,595 = <strong>&euro;45,405</strong>.
  </p>
  <p>
    <strong>Step 3 &mdash; IRPEF calculation:</strong> Because &euro;45,405 falls across two brackets, the tax is calculated progressively:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>23% on the first &euro;28,000 = &euro;6,440</li>
    <li>35% on the remaining &euro;17,405 (from &euro;28,001 to &euro;45,405) = &euro;6,092</li>
    <li><strong>Total gross IRPEF = &euro;12,532</strong></li>
  </ul>
  <p>
    <strong>Step 4 &mdash; Employment income deduction:</strong> For a taxable income of &euro;45,405, the detrazione per lavoro dipendente is approximately <strong>&euro;484</strong> (it decreases as income rises, reaching zero at &euro;50,000 taxable). Net IRPEF = &euro;12,532 &minus; &euro;484 = <strong>&euro;12,048</strong>.
  </p>
  <p>
    <strong>Step 5 &mdash; Regional surcharge (Lazio):</strong> Lazio applies a progressive surcharge. On &euro;45,405, the combined rate works out to approximately <strong>&euro;1,289</strong> per year (reflecting the stepped rate structure from 1.73% on the first bracket up to 3.33% on higher brackets). Consult the <a href="https://www.agenziaentrate.gov.it/portale/web/guest/addizionali-regionali" class="text-brand hover:underline">Agenzia delle Entrate regional surcharge tables</a> for exact breakpoints.
  </p>
  <p>
    <strong>Step 6 &mdash; Municipal surcharge (Rome):</strong> Rome applies a flat rate of 0.9% on taxable income: &euro;45,405 &times; 0.9% = <strong>&euro;409</strong>.
  </p>
  <p>
    <strong>Step 7 &mdash; Tax wedge 2026:</strong> At a taxable income of &euro;45,405, Alessandro <strong>does not qualify</strong> for the cuneo fiscale benefit, as it phases out completely above &euro;40,000.
  </p>

  <div class="overflow-x-auto not-prose">
    <table class="w-full text-sm border-collapse">
      <thead>
        <tr class="border-b-2 border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700">
          <th class="py-3 pr-4 text-left font-semibold text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">Item</th>
